[medium] src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue:354 (correctness)
The direct suggestions route instantiates useDashboardSuggestions before the cached feature probe has completed. Those useDataApi calls are immediate, and the mounted hook still polls after fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig without checking dashboardSuggestionsEnabled, so visiting /dashboards/suggestions/:sspId hits suggestion endpoints even when /api/dashboard-suggestions/config later says the feature is disabled or fails closed. That breaks the intended fail-closed gate and can show a broken suggestions workspace or generate 404/403 noise for a disabled feature.
Suggested fix: Gate the suggestions data endpoints and polling on the cached config: render only a loading/disabled state until fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig completes, return before pollLatest or refreshes when disabled, and make useDashboardSuggestions endpoints empty/immediate:false until enabled or instantiate the suggestions workspace only from a child rendered when enabled.
Guidance: In src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue, prevent the suggestions workspace from creating or polling suggestion endpoints until the cached AI config has been fetched and dashboardSuggestionsEnabled is true. A low-risk approach is to move the suggestion-only setup into a child component rendered with v-if="aiConfig.dashboardSuggestionsConfigFetched && aiConfig.dashboardSuggestionsEnabled" after the disabled/loading state, so useDashboardSuggestions(sspId) and useSuggestionRunPoller(...) are instantiated only when enabled. Keep the SSP title fetch if desired, but do not call refreshPendingSuggestions, refreshHistorySuggestions, pollLatest, start, generateSuggestions, acceptSuggestions, rejectSuggestions, or fetchSuggestionEvents while disabled. In the current onMounted block, after await aiConfig.fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig(), explicitly return if !aiConfig.dashboardSuggestionsEnabled before pollLatest/start. Also ensure the template shows a loading state before config is fetched and the existing disabled Message after a false/fail-closed result. Do not bypass the Pinia store or repeatedly probe config from individual components; use the cached store result.
