[medium] src/views/dashboard/partials/SuggestionScopeDialog.vue:151 (correctness)
After generate returns a server ceiling error, canGenerate stays false because ceilingError remains set. The operator can change the selected controls or label sets, but this component never emits any scope-change or clear event, and the parent only clears scopeCeilingError at the start of generate, which is now disabled. The dialog can get stuck blocking every retry until the page is refreshed.
Suggested fix: Clear the parent ceiling error when selectedControls or selectedLabelSetHashes changes, for example by emitting a scope-change event from the dialog and handling it with scopeCeilingError = , or by moving the ceiling error state into the dialog and resetting it in the selection watchers.
Guidance: In src/views/dashboard/partials/SuggestionScopeDialog.vue and its parent src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue, add a clear path for the server ceiling error when the operator changes scope. Implement an emit such as 'scope-change': [] in SuggestionScopeDialog, then add a watcher on [selectedControls, selectedLabelSetHashes] with deep: true (or watch selectedControls and selectedLabelSetHashes separately) that emits 'scope-change' and resets largeRunConfirmed to false when the user changes selection. In SuggestionsView.vue, handle @scope-change="scopeCeilingError = ''" on <SuggestionScopeDialog>. Keep clearing scopeCeilingError at the start of generate as well. Do not clear the error only inside submit/generate, because canGenerate is false while ceilingError is set and the user cannot click Generate. Avoid clearing on unrelated prop refreshes if possible; if the controls/labelSets option lists are reloaded and they change the selected arrays, clearing is acceptable because the effective scope changed.
